00:59.959 --> 01:01.859
[ Beeping ]

01:01.961 --> 01:03.861
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.230 --> 01:07.165
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:10.904 --> 01:12.872
Mmm.

01:25.351 --> 01:28.252
[ Chuckles ]
So I said to that nurse...

01:28.354 --> 01:31.517
''You can take your free
tetanus shot and shove it.''

01:31.624 --> 01:34.218
- You told her, Dad.
- You better-

01:34.327 --> 01:36.818
- [ Bones Crack ]
- believe I did.

01:36.930 --> 01:40.331
[ Grunting ]

01:40.433 --> 01:42.663
You still haven't told us
why Lenny bit you.

01:42.769 --> 01:45.101
Well, I really gave him no choice.
You see-

01:45.205 --> 01:48.197
- Lousy meat-eating scum.
- Huh?

01:48.308 --> 01:51.277
- Not you.
- [ Chomping ]

01:51.377 --> 01:55.040
I'm going over to protest this disgusting
new restaurant called The Slaughterhouse.

01:55.148 --> 01:59.175
It's decorated with hanging steer carcasses
and a fountain of blood.

01:59.285 --> 02:02.618
<i>Oh, I heard about that place
on The Red Grocer.</i>

02:02.722 --> 02:05.316
The worst part is
you pick out your own cow...

02:05.425 --> 02:07.325
and they kill it
right in front of you.

02:07.427 --> 02:10.794
Well, maybe the animals
don't mind, honey.

02:10.896 --> 02:13.457
They might enjoy being
the center of attention.

02:13.566 --> 02:15.932
I think I read somewhere
that cows like being killed.

02:16.035 --> 02:18.697
Wait! There's a place like
that in Springfield?

02:18.805 --> 02:22.241
- Then why are we eating this crap?
- [ Clanging ]

02:22.342 --> 02:26.073
Come on, everybody.
We're going to The Slaughterhouse.

02:26.179 --> 02:29.808
- You didn't need to knock the food on the floor.
- Didn't I?

02:29.916 --> 02:34.819
[ Chainsaw Revving ]

02:34.921 --> 02:38.118
[ Mooing ]

02:38.224 --> 02:43.594
Wow! It's even more wonderful
than Lisa said.

02:43.696 --> 02:47.029
Oh, whoa. A complimentary
basket of hooves.

02:47.133 --> 02:51.763
Mmm. Beef salad,
beef on the cob, beef-fried beef-

02:51.871 --> 02:53.998
Is there anything on the menu
that isn't meat?

02:54.107 --> 02:56.337
- Ha. Not likely.
- Cool.

02:56.442 --> 03:00.378
Even this menu is made of meat.
It's an entire chicken pounded flat.

03:00.480 --> 03:03.847
How clever.
The kids' menu is on the beak.

03:03.950 --> 03:07.750
Hmm, I think I'll take-
oh, that one.

03:07.854 --> 03:09.754
<i>- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Thud ]</i>

03:09.856 --> 03:11.824
No. He's a bit listless, isn't he?

03:11.925 --> 03:14.587
Give me-
ooh, that spirited fellow.

03:14.727 --> 03:16.592
<i>- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Thud ]</i>

03:16.696 --> 03:20.223
He didn't put up much of a fight.
Why don't you pick one for me?

03:20.333 --> 03:22.426
<i>- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Thud ]</i>

03:22.535 --> 03:25.060
On second thought,
I'll just have a glass of milk...

03:25.171 --> 03:27.935
- from that cow.
- Hmm?

03:28.041 --> 03:29.531
<i>- [ Gunshot ]
- [ Thud ]</i>

03:29.642 --> 03:32.702
<i>[ Homer ] Wait a minute.
Is this the biggest steak you've got?</i>

03:32.812 --> 03:36.714
Seventy-two ounces? I thought this
was supposed to be a steak house...

03:36.816 --> 03:41.981
not a little girlie, underpantsie,
pink-doily, tea-party place.

03:42.088 --> 03:45.421
Well, there is one steak that's
only available by special request.

03:45.525 --> 03:49.154
We call it ''Sirloin-a-Lot.''
It's the size of a boogie board.

03:49.262 --> 03:52.789
Ooh! I'll have that one.
And to drink, meatballs.

03:52.899 --> 03:55.766
- Very good, sir.
- [ Dinging ]

03:55.868 --> 04:00.737
Ladies and gentlemen, this brave man
has accepted the ''Sirloin-a-Lot'' challenge.

04:00.840 --> 04:05.038
He will pit his stomach against
1 6 pounds of indomitable tenderloin.

04:05.144 --> 04:08.602
<i>- [ People Oohing ]
- They like me because I'm brave.</i>

04:08.715 --> 04:12.412
Only two people have ever
finished the whole thing.

04:14.053 --> 04:16.248
If you want some friendly advice, pal...

04:16.356 --> 04:18.255
I wouldn't tackle the big one right away.

04:18.358 --> 04:21.122
Oh, yeah?
What do you know about it?

04:29.068 --> 04:32.560
- Hmm?
- It's you! You're him!

04:32.672 --> 04:34.606
You're Tony Randall!

04:34.707 --> 04:37.699
[ Chuckles ]
Red Barclay's my name. I'm a trucker.

04:37.810 --> 04:40.973
And I've eaten steaks from coast
to coast with taters and toast.

04:41.080 --> 04:44.447
Take my advice.
This one's not for greenhorns.

04:44.550 --> 04:49.419
Greenhorn? Who's a greenhorn?
What's a greenhorn?

04:49.522 --> 04:52.218
It's an insult. Sock him, Dad.
Sock everybody.

04:52.325 --> 04:57.627
Oh, you're just jealous 'cause you don't have
the belly for it anymore, Mr. No-Belly.

04:57.730 --> 05:00.198
Mr. Hasn't-Got-A-Belly.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.325
Well, I have just
finished a whole lamb.

05:02.435 --> 05:06.098
But, uh, I reckon I could
take you to school. You're on, boy.

05:06.272 --> 05:08.763
<i>- ##[ Fanfare ]
- [ Grunting ]</i>

05:08.875 --> 05:11.742
[ Drooling ]

05:11.844 --> 05:14.244
Is it safe to eat that much food,
Dr. Hibbert?

05:14.347 --> 05:17.578
You know, I wouldn't have thought so before
I bought 1 2% percent of this restaurant...

05:17.684 --> 05:21.711
but now I feel a balanced diet can include
the occasional eating contest.

05:21.821 --> 05:25.018
- But what if he chokes?
- Oh, not to worry.

05:25.124 --> 05:27.251
We have the latest Heimlich machine.

05:27.360 --> 05:30.329
[ Gagging ]

05:34.600 --> 05:39.003
On your left, the pride of
the American trucking industry...

05:39.105 --> 05:43.804
<i>- ''Reliable'' Red Barclay!
- [ Cheering, Applause ]</i>

05:43.910 --> 05:45.810
And an your right,
Homer somebody.

05:45.912 --> 05:48.437
- Go, Dad! Go, go, go!
- Yeah! Come on, Homie!

05:48.548 --> 05:52.382
Gluttons, to your marks,
and gorge!

05:54.454 --> 05:58.754
Chew, chew, chew!
Chew, chew, chew!

05:58.858 --> 06:01.850
- Ooh, dear.
- No, Homer! Don't fill up on bread!

06:01.961 --> 06:03.861
Huh? Oh, right! The steak!

06:03.963 --> 06:05.931
[ Chomping ]

06:08.234 --> 06:11.931
Come on, Dad. Pick up the pace.
Chew and swallow. No savoring.

06:12.038 --> 06:16.600
Must eat beef.
Must defeat guy I just met.

06:17.877 --> 06:19.902
[ Chomping ]

06:20.012 --> 06:22.879
[ Chomping ]

06:22.982 --> 06:24.882
So much steak.

06:24.984 --> 06:28.476
Lungs filling.
Sinuses packed with meat.

06:28.588 --> 06:30.954
Come on, Dad.
Just 1 2 more pounds.

06:31.057 --> 06:33.651
[ Groaning ]

06:33.760 --> 06:35.990
Oh, humans are so ridiculous.

06:36.095 --> 06:39.826
He's not even halfway through Walter
and he's already hallucinating.

06:39.932 --> 06:41.957
[ Both Laughing ]

06:42.068 --> 06:45.401
Lousy drunks!
I'll show them!

06:48.374 --> 06:50.740
[ Groaning ]

06:55.648 --> 06:57.673
What's happening to me?

06:57.784 --> 07:00.685
There's still food,
but I don't want to eat it.

07:00.787 --> 07:05.247
I've become everything
I've ever hated. [ Sobbing ]

07:07.326 --> 07:10.159
<i>- Mmm.
- [ Cheering, Applause ]</i>

07:10.263 --> 07:15.633
The winner and still champion,
''Reliable'' Red Barclay!

07:15.735 --> 07:19.466
My hat's off to you, Red.
You're a true American hero.

07:19.572 --> 07:22.905
And you did it with style and dignity.
And- Hey!

07:23.009 --> 07:24.909
You're not breathing.

07:25.011 --> 07:26.945
Don't people usually breathe?

07:29.115 --> 07:32.346
This man is dead.
Looks to me like beef poisoning.

07:32.452 --> 07:35.421
- [ All Gasping ]
- Probably from some other restaurant.

07:35.521 --> 07:37.887
- [ All Sighing ]
- [ Man ] Pass the ribs.

07:42.228 --> 07:44.594
[ Grunting ]

07:44.697 --> 07:47.097
You'd better take one of these too.
He's eaten quite a lot.

07:47.200 --> 07:49.100
[ Tires Squealing ]

07:49.202 --> 07:51.966
There goes the finest trucker
who ever lived.

07:52.071 --> 07:54.403
He called me greenhorn.

07:54.507 --> 07:58.204
I called him Tony Randall.
It was a thing we had.

07:58.311 --> 08:01.303
In 38 years,
he never missed a shipment.

08:01.414 --> 08:04.906
But I guess this is one delivery
old Red won't be making.

08:05.017 --> 08:09.317
Oh, yes, he will.
And on time too.

08:09.422 --> 08:11.982
Oh, no. Homer, no.

08:12.091 --> 08:16.152
I've got to, honey. I owe it to old Red
as both his friend and his killer.

08:16.262 --> 08:18.196
Oh, let me go with you, Dad.

08:18.297 --> 08:20.265
- Don't you have school?
- Don't you have work?

08:20.366 --> 08:21.594
Ah, touche!

08:21.701 --> 08:23.669
Bye, Marge!

08:24.770 --> 08:27.898
- Aren't you gonna say bye?
- Good-bye, Homer.

08:28.007 --> 08:30.874
- That didn't sound like you meant it.
- Oh, all right.

08:30.977 --> 08:33.241
Good-bye, sweetheart.
Have a nice trip.

08:33.346 --> 08:36.577
That's more like it.
So long, suckers!

08:36.682 --> 08:40.082
<i>- [ Homer Laughing ]
- [ Horn Honks ]</i>

08:44.524 --> 08:46.685
[ Grinding ]

08:46.792 --> 08:50.421
<i>- [ Homer Grunting ]
- [ Grinding Continues ]</i>

08:50.530 --> 08:54.193
- [ Grunting ] Come on!
- [ Grinding ]

08:54.300 --> 08:56.632
Ah, now I'm getting
the hang of this thing.

08:56.736 --> 09:00.604
- I don't know why
I didn't become a trucker before.
- You're not really a trucker now.

09:00.706 --> 09:03.834
Oh, yeah?
My left arm says different.

09:03.943 --> 09:06.707
Well, according to Red's schedule,
we have to make it to Atlanta in three days.

09:06.812 --> 09:08.746
Piece of cake.
Just need a little truck-driving music.

09:18.291 --> 09:20.987
Yeah. The open road.

09:21.093 --> 09:22.958
## [ Ends ]

09:24.797 --> 09:28.164
Ah, that little punk.
I'll teach him some manners!

09:29.802 --> 09:32.737
- [ Screams ]
- No, Dad! He wants you to blow your horn.

09:32.838 --> 09:34.430
Oh.

09:36.709 --> 09:39.143
<i>[ Homer ]
That little punk.!</i>

09:40.546 --> 09:41.681
Lisa, we got another postcard
from your father.

09:41.681 --> 09:41.976
Lisa, we got another postcard
from your father.

09:48.621 --> 09:50.748
Wow! Dad and Bart
have been everywhere.

09:50.856 --> 09:54.451
They've eaten submarine sandwiches,
grinders and hoagies.

09:54.560 --> 09:58.929
It's not fair. Your father always gets to
have such exciting adventures.

09:59.031 --> 10:02.558
Maybe it's time we took
a walk on the wild side.

10:04.470 --> 10:06.404
We're buying a new doorbell?

10:06.505 --> 10:08.473
A musical doorbell.

10:10.610 --> 10:15.309
So many doorbells.
I'm in way over my head.

10:15.414 --> 10:18.781
## [ Humming ]

10:18.884 --> 10:22.115
- [ Rings ]
- [ Chuckles ]

10:22.221 --> 10:24.121
[ Grunting ]

10:24.223 --> 10:27.192
Oh, great!
Look at my shoes.

10:27.293 --> 10:30.888
And today's my evaluation
with Senor Ding-Dong.

10:30.997 --> 10:35.696
Excuse me, Mr.... Trainee,
I'm trying to find a musical doorbell.

10:35.801 --> 10:38.292
Well, you came to the right place.

10:38.404 --> 10:43.774
We got your ding-dang-dongs and
your do-re-mis and your ha-cha-chas, huh?

10:43.876 --> 10:46.504
[ Chuckles, Mumbles ]

10:46.612 --> 10:49.080
I'm trying to find a particular tune.

10:49.181 --> 10:53.550
It's the one that goes like-
## [ Humming ]

10:53.653 --> 10:58.386
- Mom, is this the one you want?
- ## [ Pop ]

10:58.491 --> 11:00.721
Yes! That's it!

11:00.826 --> 11:03.226
Lisa, you ought to be
a doorbell salesman.

11:03.329 --> 11:05.957
Oh, that's just what I need.
Another piranha in the tank.

11:06.065 --> 11:09.034
<i>##[Jukebox:Rock ]</i>

11:09.135 --> 11:12.969
- A little more high test, darlin'?
- Sure thing, Gwen.

11:13.072 --> 11:15.734
I'll be right back
with your pie, hon.

11:15.841 --> 11:19.174
- Ah, that's a nice, friendly gal.
- Yeah.

11:19.278 --> 11:21.906
Wouldn't it be great to live
right here at the truck stop?

11:22.014 --> 11:23.914
Watching all the people
come and go.

11:24.016 --> 11:27.452
- You could have a different best friend every day.
- I suppose.

11:27.553 --> 11:30.454
Great. Now write your mother
and tell her the marriage is off.

11:30.556 --> 11:34.424
And then when the paperwork is done,
I'll make Gwen my wife.

11:34.527 --> 11:36.722
- Will that be all, sweetie?
- For now.

11:36.829 --> 11:40.526
The light's on.
All systems are ding-dong.

11:40.633 --> 11:42.624
Come on, Mom.
Let's take it for a test drive.

11:42.735 --> 11:46.762
It's not a toy, Lisa. We'll just have to
wait until someone comes.

11:48.140 --> 11:50.506
Anyone?
Anyone at all?

11:50.609 --> 11:53.703
Oh! Milhouse is selling seeds,
and he's coming this way-

11:53.813 --> 11:55.747
Oh, the birds got him.

11:55.848 --> 11:58.783
[ Screaming ]
Not the face!

11:58.884 --> 12:01.978
If your father was here,
there'd be process servers, repo men...

12:02.088 --> 12:03.988
and bounty hunters
to beat the band.

12:04.090 --> 12:05.990
Wait! People are coming!

12:06.092 --> 12:08.185
- I think they'reJehovah's Witnesses.
- Yes!

12:09.762 --> 12:11.821
Wait, Marlin. You know,
I just had a thought.

12:11.931 --> 12:14.923
Maybe we're bothering people by
trying to change their religion.

12:15.034 --> 12:17.002
What if we don't
have all the answers?

12:17.103 --> 12:20.368
You're right, Nureen.
Let's go get real jobs.

12:22.742 --> 12:25.404
Oh. I would have feigned interest.

12:26.445 --> 12:29.642
## [ Humming ]

12:29.749 --> 12:31.649
Still no visitors.

12:31.751 --> 12:34.777
It's time we opened up a can
of Whup-Tushie on this situation.

12:34.887 --> 12:36.787
What's the number for Luigi's?

12:36.889 --> 12:39.824
Dad's got it on the speed dial
under ''fire.''

12:41.727 --> 12:44.423
This is it, honey.
We did it.

12:44.530 --> 12:46.430
- Damn it!
- Oh.

12:46.532 --> 12:49.865
<i>- [ Marge ] Ring the bell.!
- Why? You already know I'm here, don't you?</i>

12:49.969 --> 12:52.494
<i>- [ Marge ]Just do it.!
- Nothing doin', missy.</i>

12:52.605 --> 12:55.039
Now do you want your half order
of garlic bread or not?

12:55.141 --> 12:57.905
<i>- No. But if you'll just ring the-
- [ Tires Squealing ]</i>

12:58.010 --> 12:59.773
Oh, that's it.
I'm putting an end to this.

12:59.879 --> 13:02.313
- Lisa, no, no, don't! It won't be the-
- ## [ Pop ]

13:02.414 --> 13:05.906
Oh. It's heavenly.

13:06.018 --> 13:08.919
## [ Singing ]

13:12.525 --> 13:14.516
Why is it playing over again?

13:14.627 --> 13:17.494
Who cares? No one could ever
get sick of this song.

13:17.596 --> 13:19.587
## [ Singing ]

13:19.698 --> 13:22.223
<i>##[ Suspenseful ]</i>

13:22.334 --> 13:25.201
<i>[ Man ]
Hey, get that truck out ofhere.!</i>

13:25.304 --> 13:26.703
[ Chomping ]

13:26.806 --> 13:31.209
- [ Woman ] You mean, it ate Patrick too?
- It ate everybody.

13:31.310 --> 13:33.175
What about Erica?

13:33.279 --> 13:36.680
- It ate everybody!
- It ate everybody, stupid!

13:38.751 --> 13:43.085
I bet old Red caught himself a mess
of catfish with these fishing sticks.

13:43.189 --> 13:47.421
- Uh-huh. I bet he used bait.
- Relax, boy. We're ahead of schedule.

13:47.526 --> 13:50.222
Actually, we have to go
2,200 miles in 1 0 hours.

13:50.329 --> 13:52.490
Ten hours?
We gotta roll!

13:57.069 --> 14:01.597
Uh, yeah. I need something that'll keep me
awake, alert and reckless all night long.

14:01.707 --> 14:05.939
Well, Congress is racing back
to Washington to outlaw these.

14:06.045 --> 14:10.573
- Sold!
- Hey, you can't that many pep pills at once.

14:10.683 --> 14:14.084
No problem. I'll balance it out
with a bottle of sleeping pills.

14:14.186 --> 14:16.086
[ Chomping ]

14:16.188 --> 14:20.090
[ Giggling ] Okay, we're all set.
Let's put the pedal to the metal.

14:23.562 --> 14:25.689
I wholeheartedly agree!
Oh, man, I'm really wired.

14:25.798 --> 14:27.732
This is a big mistake. I-

14:27.833 --> 14:32.827
Oh, here come the sleeping pills.
So drowsy.

14:32.938 --> 14:37.773
Pep pills! Perking up again!
I could drive all... night.

14:37.877 --> 14:40.107
[ Snoring ]

14:42.448 --> 14:43.972
[ Both Snoring ]

14:48.954 --> 14:52.788
- [ Snoring ]
- [ Beeping ]

14:56.829 --> 14:59.855
[ Tires Squealing ]

15:03.502 --> 15:06.335
<i>- [ Bell Dings ]
- [ Snoring ]</i>

15:06.438 --> 15:09.635
Huh? [ Screams ]
I fell asleep at the wheel!

15:09.742 --> 15:11.801
Hey.
[ Mumbles ]

15:11.911 --> 15:12.511
But we didn't crash.
It's a miracle!

15:12.511 --> 15:12.875
But we didn't crash.
It's a miracle!

15:19.485 --> 15:22.579
I fell asleep at the wheel,
and the truck drove here by itself.

15:22.688 --> 15:27.125
Yeah. That Navi-Tron Auto-Drive
System has made our jobs cushier than ever.

15:27.226 --> 15:29.421
- The what now?
- You know, this thing.

15:29.528 --> 15:31.462
With this baby driving
your truck for you...

15:31.563 --> 15:34.896
all you gotta do is sit back
and feel your ass grow.

15:35.000 --> 15:37.298
- The trucks drive themselves?
- Shh! Hey, hey. Shh!

15:37.403 --> 15:39.837
Didn't your union rep tell you
about the scam we got going?

15:39.939 --> 15:42.908
I'm not really a trucker,
so I don't talk to the rep that often.

15:43.008 --> 15:45.636
All right, listen, pal.
Here's the deal.

15:45.744 --> 15:48.736
You stumbled on the secret that only
truck drivers are supposed to know.

15:48.847 --> 15:50.747
[ Laughing ]

15:50.849 --> 15:53.784
- Hey, pay attention and stop
looking at that squirrel.
- [ Chittering ]

15:53.886 --> 15:56.548
We get 40 bucks an hour
to drive these rigs.

15:56.655 --> 15:59.852
Do you think anybody would hire us if they
knew we weren't really driving the trucks?

15:59.959 --> 16:03.417
Wow! You guys are even
lazier than me.

16:03.529 --> 16:07.727
- Well, don't worry. I'll keep your secret.
- See that you do.

16:10.836 --> 16:14.465
- Hey, Bart. Watch me run down this old lady.
- Dad, no!

16:16.408 --> 16:19.036
- [ Beeps ]
- [ Screams ]

16:19.144 --> 16:21.112
[ Laughing ]

16:21.213 --> 16:24.341
The second I let go of the wheel,
this little wonder kicks in.

16:24.450 --> 16:28.716
And if scaring old ladies don't
float your boat, watch this! [ Grunts ]

16:29.955 --> 16:33.118
Come on out, boy!
It's windy!

16:34.226 --> 16:37.059
Wow! You're right, Dad.
It is windy!

16:39.631 --> 16:41.531
Hey, look. Nobody's driving.

16:41.633 --> 16:43.567
Well, will wonders never cease?

16:43.669 --> 16:49.107
Relax, everybody. The Navi-Tron Auto-Drive
System is driving the truck for me.

16:49.208 --> 16:52.666
But keep it a secret.
It's a big scam, okay?

16:54.346 --> 16:56.211
[ Shutters Clicking ]

16:59.151 --> 17:01.278
What the hell?
Breaker, breaker.

17:01.387 --> 17:03.981
Looks like we got us a 1 0-38.

17:05.723 --> 17:08.954
Uh, 1 0-38. Uh, let's see.

17:09.060 --> 17:12.428
Uh, ''outsider blabbing
about auto-drive system.''

17:12.531 --> 17:15.397
Well, we'll have to teach
our friend some discretion.

17:15.501 --> 17:20.131
- Yeah.Just like we did toJimmy Hoffa. [ Chuckles ]
- Hey, shut up!

17:20.239 --> 17:23.976
Calling all big rigs. Motormouth
on Highway 7. You know what to do.

17:30.649 --> 17:31.616
I need to get some sleep.

17:31.717 --> 17:33.446
I have a test tomorrow in-
[ Quoting Lyrics ] I mean, English.

17:33.552 --> 17:36.077
Okay, okay. Let me just
get the wire cutters.

17:36.188 --> 17:41.182
Oh. Your father traded
our tools for M&M's again.

17:41.293 --> 17:43.591
Oh, the heck with it.
[ Groans ]

17:43.695 --> 17:45.890
<i>##[ Playing Faster ]</i>

17:45.998 --> 17:48.796
<i>- ##[ Continues, Faster ]
- [ Dogs Howling ]</i>

17:48.901 --> 17:51.461
<i>##[ Continues, Faster, Louder ]</i>

17:57.609 --> 18:01.739
Look, Son. It's one of nature's
most beautiful sights.

18:01.847 --> 18:04.042
The convoy!

18:07.086 --> 18:10.021
- He hit us!
- Oh, I should have known.

18:10.122 --> 18:14.786
<i>- They're hazing us to initiate us
into the truckers' fraternity.
- [ Crash ]</i>

18:14.893 --> 18:17.293
Thank you, sir!
May I have another?

18:17.396 --> 18:22.527
- Dad, they're trying to kill us!
- Oh, why do all my trips end like this?

18:26.738 --> 18:30.105
- Eat water, good buddy!
- [ Screams ]

18:30.209 --> 18:32.006
Whoa! Look at him roll!

18:32.111 --> 18:34.443
[ Grunts ]

18:34.546 --> 18:38.175
Oh! My good knife!
My wife's gonna kill me.

18:38.283 --> 18:40.843
<i>- [ Homer ] I think we lost 'em, Bart.
- Dad, stop!</i>

18:43.355 --> 18:46.722
<i>Uh-oh. Well, well, well.</i>

18:46.825 --> 18:50.761
Looks like we got ourselves
a showdown, boy.

18:50.863 --> 18:52.831
- All right.
- What are you doing?

18:52.931 --> 18:56.628
- I'm keeping a promise
to an American roadmaster.
- Huh?

18:56.735 --> 19:00.398
Red! The trucker!

19:00.506 --> 19:03.532
- Big fat guy couldn't handle his steak?
- Oh, yeah.

19:03.642 --> 19:05.837
- We'll get past that barrier somehow.
- [ Beeping ]

19:05.944 --> 19:08.913
Old Blinky here will find a way.

19:09.014 --> 19:12.245
- [ Engine Revving ]
- [ Tires Squealing ]

19:12.351 --> 19:16.253
I'm afraid I can't let you do this, Red.
The risk is unacceptable.

19:16.355 --> 19:17.879
I'm not Red.
I'm Homer.

19:17.990 --> 19:19.423
- Gotta go!
- Uh-oh.

19:20.993 --> 19:23.052
- [ Screams ]
- Dad, do something.

19:23.162 --> 19:25.130
Something better!

19:25.230 --> 19:28.393
[ Screaming ]

19:28.500 --> 19:32.027
<i>[ Both Screaming ]</i>

19:32.137 --> 19:35.834
[ Screaming Continues ]

19:35.941 --> 19:38.000
Whoo-hoo!

19:38.110 --> 19:42.479
Now that man is a genuine, steel-belted,
gear-jamming rig jockey.

19:42.581 --> 19:44.071
- That's a fact.
- Boy howdy.

19:44.183 --> 19:45.775
- You can say that again.
- Yeah.

19:45.884 --> 19:49.479
Boys, I've been thinking. Maybe it's time
we ditched the high-tech gizmos...

19:49.588 --> 19:51.647
and went back to driving
like our daddies did.

19:51.757 --> 19:53.748
- Drunk?
- No! No.

19:53.859 --> 19:56.054
Using our hands and our wits.

19:56.161 --> 19:58.527
Yeah, sure it's hard work
and it's lonely as hell.

19:58.630 --> 20:01.531
But it has meaning and dignity.
Huh? What do you say?

20:04.836 --> 20:07.566
Nah. Let's just find some other scam.

20:07.673 --> 20:10.164
Hey, how about bootlegging
Beanie Babies?

20:10.275 --> 20:13.073
- Sounds good to me.
- Oh, I like that.

20:16.248 --> 20:18.148
Yep, you're gonna make it, Dad.

20:18.250 --> 20:20.775
Somewhere up there,
I bet Red is saying thanks.

20:21.954 --> 20:23.751
1 0-4, dead buddy.

20:26.725 --> 20:31.025
This is Red Barclay's shipment,
on time as always.

20:31.129 --> 20:33.097
All right, let's see.

20:33.198 --> 20:37.328
Artichokes and migrant workers.
Looking good.

20:37.436 --> 20:39.336
So where is old Red anyway?

20:39.438 --> 20:42.601
Well, the last time I saw him,
he was in a big plastic bag.

20:42.708 --> 20:45.836
Ha. Yeah, that sounds
like Red, all right.

20:45.944 --> 20:49.675
Well, Son, I guess
it's time to go home.

20:49.781 --> 20:52.215
Any thoughts on how
we're gonna get there?

20:52.317 --> 20:57.016
No. But I'm sure
the Good Lord will provide.

20:57.122 --> 21:00.888
Are you crazy? I'm not driving
a trainload of napalm to Springfield!

21:01.927 --> 21:03.622
Thank you.

21:08.200 --> 21:10.828
- ## [ Pop ]
- [ All Shouting ]

21:10.936 --> 21:14.633
I'm really sorry, everybody.
But I've tried everything.

21:14.740 --> 21:17.766
I'm afraid we're just going to
have to learn to live with it.

21:17.876 --> 21:20.003
No, no, no.
No dice!

21:20.112 --> 21:24.515
All right, Chimey,
this time the bell tolls for thee.

21:24.616 --> 21:27.210
Huh?

21:27.319 --> 21:29.810
<i>Ayayay.! Senor Ding-Dong!</i>

21:29.921 --> 21:31.946
- ## [ Continues ]
- I thought you were just a marketing gimmick.

21:32.057 --> 21:37.120
There was a time when that was true.
But now I am so much more.

21:37.229 --> 21:39.493
<i>- ## [ Stops ]
- [ Crowd Cheering ]</i>

21:39.598 --> 21:42.965
<i>Oh, my.
Gracias, senor.</i>

21:43.068 --> 21:48.870
<i>De nada.
If you ever need me,just ring.</i>

21:49.975 --> 21:53.467
[ Engine Cranking ]

21:53.578 --> 21:55.808
Does anyone have any jumper cables?

21:55.914 --> 21:58.678
<i>[ Engine Cranks, Stops ]</i>

21:58.784 --> 22:01.252
<i>[ Senor Ding-Dong ]
Oh,you stinking Chevy.!</i>

22:41.326 --> 22:43.294
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

